When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
  when you use multiple computers, want to back up your files online, or want to collaborate with others.

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
  If you are working with others you might not want to pull everything

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches. When would you use one instead of another?
  Fork - github only version of clones
  Clone - works in both, copies an entire repository
  branch - subsections of repositories that can be modified independently
